The Quest is a 1996 American martial arts film directed by Jean-Claude Van Damme his directorial debut, who also starred in the lead role. The film co-stars Roger Moore, James Remar and Janet Gunn. The film was released in the United States on April 26, 1996.The plot revolves around an international martial arts tournament. Claims by Frank Dux that it was a rework of a script Frank Dux wrote entitled "The Kumite" were rejected by a jury.
